NUMBER 1028
NAME Southern Island, Sandy Shore
REGION 38
OUTDOOR_FLOOR
DAY_LIGHT
CHANNEL 26
EXIT NE 1029
EXIT SE 1066
EXIT ABOVE 2341
*DESCRIPTION_START
Fine crimson sand shifts softly underfoot and extends for what seems like miles curving around the coast of the island. A short distance back from the ocean itself, a sheer cliff rises toward the sky, blocking passage to the interior of the island.
*DESCRIPTION_END
;
NUMBER 1029
NAME Southern Island, Tangled Vegetation
Region 38
OUTDOOR_FLOOR
DAY_LIGHT
CHANNEL 26
EXIT SW 1028
EXIT ABOVE 2341
MONSTER_GROUP 45
*DESCRIPTION_START
The sandy shore rapidly gives way to dense vegetation. Thick tangles of vines climb up all available surfaces, forming impassable nets between the trunks of trees. The air is heavy and moist, and filled with the buzz and whine of insect life.
*DESCRIPTION_END
ITEM 0 664
ITEM 9 693
*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAM 0
Dark, heavy vines wrap around the trees and sprawl along the shore, choking out all other vegetation. Beneath them you can almost make out the shapes of what lays beneath.
*DESCRIPTION_END

NUMBER 1066
NAME Southern Island, Cliff Side
Region 38
OUTDOOR_FLOOR
DAY_LIGHT
CHANNEL 26
EXIT NW 1028
EXIT U 1068
EXIT ABOVE 2340
ITEM 9 693
*DESCRIPTION_START
The crimson sand shifts underfoot, making walking difficult. The jungle to the north slowly encroaches on the beach, sending out tendrils of vine to crawl over the sand and twine over and around anything that stands still long enough. Through an opening in the wall of vegetation, a path leads up the side of the cliff.
*Description_END

NUMBER 1068
NAME Southern Island, Cliff Path
Region 38
OUTDOOR_FLOOR
DAY_LIGHT
CHANNEL 26
EXIT D 1066
EXIT U 2238
*DESCRIPTION_START
The path continues climbing the steep side of the cliff. Thick vines and
creepers form a living canopy above. Flowers and plants of every
description thrive in the warm, moist air. Mosquitoes and other
insects flutter and buzz against the net that encloses the path.
*DESCRIPTION_END
;
NUMBER 2238
NAME Southern Island, Cliff Path
Region 38
OUTDOOR_FLOOR
DAY_LIGHT
CHANNEL 26
;
EXIT U 2239
EXIT D 1068

;
*DESCRIPTION_START
The path continues to wind around the slope of the cliff, dropping off
sharply on one side, bounded by heavy vegetation on the other. From this
vantage, the entire southern side of the island is visible. Above you, the
thick plants and vines give way to shining basalt. Mosquito netting is
strung over poles, keeping the insect life at bay.
*DESCRIPTION_END
IFPREVERB GAZE -1
  ECHO PLAYER Deep green and lush, the ever-present vines blanket the cliffside. The vague shapes barely discernible from below stand out sharply from this height.
  ECHO PLAYER Paler green lines run through the emerald of the vines in a symmetrical pattern of spokes radiating from the slope on which you stand.
ENDIF
;
NUMBER 2239
NAME Southern Island
Region 38
OUTDOOR_FLOOR
DAY_LIGHT
CHANNEL 26
CALL 19
;
EXIT U 2240
EXIT D 2238
*DESCRIPTION_START
The air is cooler above the jungle canopy, and breathing is easier without
the heavy moisture. Glassy obsidian crunches underfoot, making walking a
dangerous proposition. Even here, though, the tenacious vines have
encroached, sending thin creepers to seek purchase through the rock into
the soil below. Mosquito netting keeps insects off the path.
*DESCRIPTION_END
IFENTRY
  RANDOM DUMMY1 1 50 0
  IFVAR DUMMY1 < 10
    ECHO PLAYER You miss your footing and skid down the slope.
    ECHO OTHERS %n slips on the loose rock and slides down the slope.
    MOVE 2238
    DAMAGEPLR BODYONLY 20 The glass-like rocks slash at you, drawing blood.
    POSITION LAY
    AFFECT 2238
    ECHO OTHERS %n skids down from above, sprawling in a heap at your feet.
  ENDIF
ENDIF

;
NUMBER 2240
NAME Southern Island, Lip of the Crater
Region 38
OUTDOOR_FLOOR
DAY_LIGHT
CHANNEL 26
EXIT D 2239

EXIT ABOVE 2341
EXIT BELOW 1501
*DESCRIPTION_START
The entire island spreads out below you, a tapestry of rich emeralds with
jewel-toned accents. The sea stretches for miles in every direction, but
here and there, other islands dot the surface. The crumbling lip curves
around, framing the mouth of a hollowed depression. The sides are steep and
offer no purchase for climbing, but looking down into the hollow, you notice
ledges carved out of the sheer rock at intervals. A narrow path leads out to
a flat rock.
*DESCRIPTION_END
ITEM 0 74 VAL2=2240
NUMBER 1501
NAME Southern Island, Upper Crater
Region 38
OUTDOOR_FLOOR
DAY_LIGHT
CHANNEL 26
EXIT ABOVE 2240
EXIT BELOW 1502
MONSTER_GROUP 46
*DESCRIPTION_START
Just below the lip of the crater, a wide ledge circles the hollow. Lichen
has overgrown the smoothed rock, making mottled patterns of glowing green
and blue against the black of the igneous rock. Here and there, deep shadows
suggest openings that lead inside the glassy walls of the extinct volcano.
An eerie chittering rises from the depths of the bowl.
*DESCRIPTION_END
